App download and initial setup:
git clone https://github.com/xaviercsc/phonedirectoryapp.git
cd phonedirectoryapp

Streamlit local run and tests ;
python -m venv myenv
source myenv/bin/activate
pip install -r  requirements.txt
streamlit run main.py


docker build instructions:
docker build -t meandatainc/phone-directory-app .
docker login -u meandatainc
docker push meandatainc/phone-directory-app

docker run -p 8501:8501 meandatainc/phone-directory-app

docker run -e AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=xxxxxxxxx \
           -e AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=xxxxxxxx \
           -e AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=xxxxx \
           -p 8501:8501 meandatainc/phone-directory-app


AWS CLI local linux pc setup :
sudo apt update
sudo apt install unzip
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install
aws --version
aws configure


Push Docker image  from local pc to AWS ECR repository:
create a repository in AWS ECR : phoneappimage
create a AWS S3 bucket : phonedirectorybucket

aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin 016963197464.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com
docker tag meandatainc/phone-directory-app:latest 016963197464.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/phoneappimage:latest
docker push 016963197464.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/phoneappimage:latest

-------------------------------------
Terraform option :
export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID="your_access_key_id"
export AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY="your_secret_access_key"
export AWS_DEFAULT_REGION="us-east-1"




